# Lesson Authoring Rules

Apply these rules when editing lesson Markdown in `web-foundations/docs/**/*.md`.

## Code block categories

Every code block must be explicitly treated as one of:

- `CodeSandbox-ready`
- `Excerpt`
- `Template`

Add a short note near the first code section so the reader knows the convention.

## CodeSandbox-ready standard

Only mark a block `CodeSandbox-ready` if it is genuinely copy-paste ready:

- imports included
- root component or complete file structure included when needed
- no missing app shell
- no hidden globals
- no undefined helpers
- no fake completeness

Prefer complete JavaScript / JSX examples unless the lesson explicitly requires another language.

## Excerpt standard

Mark blocks as `Excerpt` when they are:

- partial
- conceptual
- pseudocode
- shader fragments
- utility-only snippets that rely on external setup

Do not imply that excerpts run as-is.

## Template standard

Mark blocks as `Template` when they are intended to be customized:

- config files
- prompt skeletons
- starter documents
- examples with placeholders

Always state what must be replaced or adapted.

## Sandbox architecture: multi-file with routes

Lessons with more than one runnable example MUST use a **routed multi-file sandbox**. Never replace `App.jsx` for each example.

### Structure

```
src/
  main.jsx                  ← providers + CSS import (set up once)
  App.jsx                   ← NavBar + Routes (all examples pre-wired)
  services/                 ← shared API functions (fetch, create, delete, gqlRequest)
  components/               ← reusable UI (cards, status messages, forms)
  pages/
    Home.jsx                ← lesson index with links to each example
    Ex1Topic.jsx            ← example 1 — imports from services/ and components/
    Ex2Topic.jsx            ← example 2
    ...
```

### Rules for Cascade

- Start the lesson with a **Sandbox setup** section: template, dependencies, config, then all scaffold files.
- `App.jsx` pre-wires ALL routes. Pages that don't exist yet will error until the student creates them.
- Each page component is self-contained: imports from `services/` and `components/`, never redefines API logic inline.
- Label page files: `**CodeSandbox-ready** — Create src/pages/ExNName.jsx.`
- Students never overwrite previous examples — they only add files.
- Scaffold files (main, App, services, components, Home) are each a separate `CodeSandbox-ready` block with target path.
- After the scaffold is complete, the preview must show a working nav bar and home page.

### Separation of concerns

- `services/` holds all data fetching (REST helpers, GraphQL client, query strings). Components never contain fetch logic.
- `components/` holds reusable UI pieces shared across example pages.
- `pages/` holds the per-example page components, each focused on one teaching concept.
- This separation is taught structurally — students learn it by building it, not by reading about it.

## Editing rule

If a block looks runnable but is not:

- either complete it fully
- or relabel it as `Excerpt` / `Template`

Never leave ambiguous runnable-looking snippets in lessons.
